hase 4 | `go test -v ./pkg/router/ -run Middleware` |\n594: | Phase 5 | `go test -v ./pkg/router/middleware/ -run Auth` |\n595: | Phase 6 | `go test -v ./pkg/router/ -run Error` |\n596: | Phase 7 | `go test -v ./pkg/router/ -run Proxy` |\n597: | Phase 8 | `go test -v ./pkg/router/ -run Config` |\n598: | Phase 9 | `go test -v ./pkg/store/ -run Redis` |\n599: | Phase 10 | `go test -v ./pkg/store/ -run Valkey` |\n600: | Phase 11 | `go test -v ./pkg/store/ -run Interface` |\n601: | Phase 12 | `go test -v ./pkg/picod/ -run Auth` |\n602: | Phase 13 | `go test -v ./pkg/picod/ -run Execute` |\n603: | Phase 14 | `go test -v ./pkg/picod/ -run File` |\n604: | Phase 15 | `go test -v ./pkg/picod/ -run Sanitize` |\n605: | Phase 16 | `go test -v ./pkg/picod/ -run Server` |\n606: | Phase 17 | `go test -coverprofile=coverage.out ./pkg/router/ ./pkg/store/ ./pkg/picod/` |\n607: | Phase 18 | `go test -race ./pkg/router/ ./pkg/store/ ./pkg/picod/` |\n608: \n609: ---\n610: \n611: ## Acceptance Criteria\n612: \n613: - [ ] All router JWT tests pass with edge cases covered\n614: - [ ] All router server tests pass including TLS and concurrency\n615: - [ ] All router session manager tests pass with validation errors\n616: - [ ] All router middleware tests pass with benchmarks\n617: - [ ] All router auth middleware tests pass with token handlers\n618: - [ ] All router error tests pass with type assertions\n619: - [ ] All router reverse proxy tests pass with header forwarding\n620: - [ ] All router config tests pass with validation\n621: - [ ] All store Redis tests pass with large data and concurrency\n622: - [ ] All store Valkey tests pass with connection errors\n623: - [ ] All store interface tests pass with singleton verification\n624: - [ ] All picod auth tests pass with PKCS1 rejection\n625: - [ ] All picod execute tests pass with signal handling\n626: - [ ] All picod file tests pass with binary handling\n627: - [ ] All picod sanitize tests pass with symlink escape prevention\n628: - [ ] All picod server tests pass with lifecycle management\n629: - [ ] Minimum 80% test coverage achieved for all packages\n630: - [ ] No race conditions detected in any package\n631: - [ ] All benchmarks execute without errors\n632: \n633: ---\n634: \n635: ## File Changes Summary\n636: \n637: | File | Action | Lines | Description |\n638: |------|--------|-------|-------------|\n639: | `pkg/router/jwt_test.go` | Modify | +80 | JWT manager edge case and benchmark tests |\n640: | `pkg/router/server_test.go` | Modify | +100 | Server handler and integration tests |\n641: | `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go` | Modify | +60 | Session manager validation and timeout tests |\n642: | `pkg/router/middleware_test.go` | Modify | +50 | Middleware concurrency and benchmark tests |\n643: | `pkg/router/middleware/auth_test.go` | Modify | +80 | Auth middleware token handler tests |\n644: | `pkg/router/errors_test.go` | Modify | +40 | Error wrapping and serialization tests |\n645: | `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go` | Modify | +60 | Proxy header forwarding and benchmark tests |\n646: | `pkg/router/config_test.go` | Modify | +30 | Config validation and immutability tests |\n647: | `pkg/store/store_test.go` | Modify | +100 | Redis store large data and benchmark tests |\n648: | `pkg/store/valkey_test.go` | Modify | +80 | Valkey connection and benchmark tests |\n649: | `pkg/picod/auth_test.go` | Modify | +60 | Auth PKCS1 rejection and benchmark tests |\n650: | `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` | Modify | +120 | Execute, files, sanitize tests enhancement |\n651: \n652: **Total: 12 modified files, ~720 new test lines**\n653: \n654: ---\n655: \n656: ## Implementation Notes\n657: \n658: ### Test Structure Guidelines\n659: \n660: 1. **Table-driven tests**: Use table-driven test patterns for multiple test cases\n661: 2. **Mock interfaces**: Use mock implementations for external dependencies\n662: 3. **Error assertions**: Use `assert.ErrorIs()` for error type checking\n663: 4. **Concurrent tests**: Use `-race` flag for thread safety verification\n664: \n665: ### Benchmark Template\n666: \n667: ```go\n668: func BenchmarkOperation(b *testing.B) {\n669:     setup := createTestSetup(b)\n670:     b.ResetTimer()\n671:     for i := 0; i < b.N; i++ {\n672:         _ = setup.performOperation()\n673:     }\n674: }\n675: ```\n676: \n677: ### Mock Store Template\n678: \n679: ```go\n680: type MockStore struct {\n681:     GetFunc    func(ctx context.Context, id string) (*SandboxInfo, error)\n682:     StoreFunc  func(ctx context.Context, sandbox *SandboxInfo) error\n683: }\n684: ```\n685: \n686: ### Coverage Target\n687: \n688: Minimum coverage requirements per package:\n689: - pkg/router: 85%\n690: - pkg/store: 90%\n691: - pkg/picod: 80%\n692: \n693: ---\n694: \n695: ## Implementation Timeline\n696: \n697: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n698: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n699: | Phase 1: Router JWT | T1.1-T1.6 | Pending | 0% |\n700: | Phase 2: Router Server | T2.1-T2.6 | Pending | 0% |\n701: | Phase 3: Router Session Manager | T3.1-T3.6 | Pending | 0% |\n702: | Phase 4: Router Middleware | T4.1-T4.5 | Pending | 0% |\n703: | Phase 5: Router Auth Middleware | T5.1-T5.6 | Pending | 0% |\n704: | Phase 6: Router Errors | T6.1-T6.4 | Pending | 0% |\n705: | Phase 7: Router Reverse Proxy | T7.1-T7.5 | Pending | 0% |\n706: | Phase 8: Router Config | T8.1-T8.3 | Pending | 0% |\n707: | Phase 9: Store Redis | T9.1-T9.6 | Pending | 0% |\n708: | Phase 10: Store Valkey | T10.1-T10.5 | Pending | 0% |\n709: | Phase 11: Store Interface | T11.1-T11.4 | Pending | 0% |\n710: | Phase 12: Picod Auth | T12.1-T12.5 | Pending | 0% |\n711: | Phase 13: Picod Execute | T13.1-T13.5 | Pending | 0% |\n712: | Phase 14: Picod Files | T14.1-T14.5 | Pending | 0% |\n713: | Phase 15: Picod Sanitize | T15.1-T15.4 | Pending | 0% |\n714: | Phase 16: Picod Server | T16.1-T16.5 | Pending | 0% |\n715: | Phase 17: Coverage Verification | T17.1-T17.5 | Pending | 0% |\n716: | Phase 18: Race Detector | T18.